1
00:00:15,140 --> 00:00:18,109
(GBRB: Farm Operation - Go Go Farm)

2
00:00:18,110 --> 00:00:20,609
(Lee Kwang Soo)

3
00:00:20,610 --> 00:00:22,709
(Kim Woo Bin)

4
00:00:22,710 --> 00:00:24,949
(Doh Kyung Soo)

5
00:00:24,950 --> 00:00:28,050
(This program contains indirect advertisements.)

6
00:00:29,590 --> 00:00:31,860
(GBRB: Farm Operation - Go Go Farm)

7
00:00:32,090 --> 00:00:35,360
(Jeju Island)

8
00:00:38,030 --> 00:00:39,260
Is it tasty?

9
00:00:41,130 --> 00:00:43,170
Let's go, Morris.

10
00:00:49,640 --> 00:00:50,810
No.

11
00:00:55,550 --> 00:00:57,520
Whoa, easy.

12
00:00:59,080 --> 00:01:00,220
Gosh, no.

13
00:01:02,790 --> 00:01:03,849
(They're on their way to feed the horses some fresh grass.)

14
00:01:03,850 --> 00:01:05,920
No.

15
00:01:07,120 --> 00:01:08,630
- Kwang Soo, look.
- Okay.

16
00:01:08,830 --> 00:01:10,330
This is where the horses are set free.

17
00:01:12,930 --> 00:01:14,000
All right, go.

18
00:01:15,470 --> 00:01:18,940
(At the pasture, the horses are excited to be let loose.)

19
00:01:20,370 --> 00:01:22,010
Gosh, it's really green.

20
00:01:24,910 --> 00:01:26,939
It feels like letting a bunch of teenage cows...

21
00:01:26,940 --> 00:01:28,580
- loose.
- Like putting them out to pasture.

22
00:01:33,120 --> 00:01:34,120
Stop it.

23
00:01:35,090 --> 00:01:36,120
It's trying to get out.

24
00:01:37,320 --> 00:01:38,320
No.

25
00:01:38,560 --> 00:01:40,929
It's going back home. Come back here.

26
00:01:40,930 --> 00:01:42,830
(One horse makes a break for it.)

27
00:01:43,060 --> 00:01:44,499
Why is it trying to go back home?

28
00:01:44,500 --> 00:01:46,230
- It wants to go back.
- Why?

29
00:01:46,400 --> 00:01:47,969
Usually, horses don't like...

30
00:01:47,970 --> 00:01:49,729
to leave their home.

31
00:01:49,730 --> 00:01:51,070
This is a brand-new environment for them.

32
00:01:52,800 --> 00:01:53,800
It's chaos.

33
00:01:53,801 --> 00:01:55,710
(The horses gallop leisurely across the meadow.)

34
00:01:56,670 --> 00:01:57,679
Goodness.

35
00:01:57,680 --> 00:01:59,240
(As a group, their homing instinct kicks in.)

36
00:01:59,610 --> 00:02:00,640
What do we do?

37
00:02:03,880 --> 00:02:04,950
Goodness.

38
00:02:06,680 --> 00:02:08,120
- No.
- What do we do?

39
00:02:09,620 --> 00:02:12,389
(The horses streak past like the wind.)

40
00:02:12,390 --> 00:02:13,660
- No.
- What do we do?

41
00:02:15,760 --> 00:02:16,760
Stop them.

42
00:02:19,900 --> 00:02:21,630
(They escape.)

43
00:02:23,970 --> 00:02:25,600
Gosh, this is a totally unexpected situation.

44
00:02:31,340 --> 00:02:32,710
Run. We have to catch them.

45
00:02:34,080 --> 00:02:35,080
This wasn't part of the plan.

46
00:02:35,110 --> 00:02:37,110
We should hurry and catch them.

47
00:02:38,480 --> 00:02:39,650
- Kwang Soo.
- Yes?

48
00:02:40,680 --> 00:02:41,920
Let's go back and catch them.

49
00:02:44,520 --> 00:02:46,289
(The horses are running so fast.)

50
00:02:46,290 --> 00:02:47,490
How do we even catch them?

51
00:02:48,790 --> 00:02:51,099
- There they are.
- They're running very fast.

52
00:02:51,100 --> 00:02:52,100
What do we do?

53
00:02:56,930 --> 00:02:58,969
(A sudden chase begins.)

54
00:02:58,970 --> 00:03:00,040
Drive ahead of them and wait there.

55
00:03:01,170 --> 00:03:03,869
- This is the ranch.
- Yes.

56
00:03:03,870 --> 00:03:05,510
Right.

57
00:03:06,380 --> 00:03:08,650
They're at the end of the ranch near the hackberry grove.

58
00:03:09,180 --> 00:03:10,919
- This is the ranch.
- Yes.

59
00:03:10,920 --> 00:03:12,149
Near the end of the campground.

60
00:03:12,150 --> 00:03:13,680
They're entering the campground now.

61
00:03:23,860 --> 00:03:29,800
(GBRB: Farm Operation - Go Go Farm)

62
00:04:42,110 --> 00:04:45,310
(A week ago)

63
00:04:45,410 --> 00:04:46,410
What?

64
00:04:47,710 --> 00:04:51,750
(The first cast member arrived.)

65
00:04:55,150 --> 00:04:56,550
- Hello.
- Hello.

66
00:04:56,720 --> 00:04:57,890
Hello.

67
00:04:58,590 --> 00:04:59,590
Hi.

68
00:04:59,591 --> 00:05:00,859
(Kwang Soo brought a straw hat.)

69
00:05:00,860 --> 00:05:01,960
It's been a long time.

70
00:05:02,590 --> 00:05:03,990
It must be hot in Jeju.

71
00:05:04,430 --> 00:05:06,360
- Actually...
- Is it not that bad?

72
00:05:07,000 --> 00:05:08,100
Look at him.

73
00:05:20,840 --> 00:05:22,609
(He shows up again today, impeccably dressed.)

74
00:05:22,610 --> 00:05:23,610
Hello.

75
00:05:26,550 --> 00:05:28,250
I thought that he was the Grim Reaper.

76
00:05:31,020 --> 00:05:32,460
Kwang Soo, how could you be dressed like that?

77
00:05:35,930 --> 00:05:37,960
You're blushing a little.

78
00:05:42,530 --> 00:05:44,030
How far is he going to take this?

79
00:05:45,970 --> 00:05:48,110
Can you even buy clothes like that?

80
00:05:48,870 --> 00:05:51,280
Maybe somewhere in Texas.

81
00:05:51,610 --> 00:05:52,740
(What?)

82
00:05:52,880 --> 00:05:54,650
Everyone is whispering as they go.

83
00:05:56,380 --> 00:05:58,650
They said, "What's with his outfit?"

84
00:06:00,450 --> 00:06:02,949
- Isn't Kyung Soo here yet?
- No, he's not.

85
00:06:02,950 --> 00:06:04,049
(They're just waiting for Kyung Soo.)

86
00:06:04,050 --> 00:06:05,559
He doesn't even go to the beauty salon.

87
00:06:05,560 --> 00:06:06,790
Kwang Soo, what time is it now?

88
00:06:07,060 --> 00:06:08,590
It's 8:56am. We're here early.

89
00:06:10,330 --> 00:06:12,500
(Just in time, Kyung Soo arrives.)

90
00:06:14,060 --> 00:06:15,170
Aren't you going to hurry?

91
00:06:16,530 --> 00:06:17,530
Aren't you going to hurry?

92
00:06:17,531 --> 00:06:19,540
This set is absolute chaos.

93
00:06:21,910 --> 00:06:24,270
Now that it's Season Four, aren't you more relaxed?

94
00:06:25,510 --> 00:06:26,880
What? It's not like I'm late.

95
00:06:27,640 --> 00:06:28,680
It's not even 9am yet.

96
00:06:30,180 --> 00:06:32,120
You think... Goodness.

97
00:06:32,720 --> 00:06:34,120
You think that I don't know it's 9am?

98
00:06:35,120 --> 00:06:36,219
Oh, my.

99
00:06:36,220 --> 00:06:38,459
What's wrong with him?

100
00:06:38,460 --> 00:06:39,460
Kyung Soo.

101
00:06:41,190 --> 00:06:42,690
You think I'm doing this because I want to?

102
00:06:43,330 --> 00:06:44,930
Every time you look at people,

103
00:06:45,500 --> 00:06:46,500
you look from one side...

104
00:06:46,501 --> 00:06:47,629
of your hat.

105
00:06:47,630 --> 00:06:49,769
(His attitude and expression are turning cowboy-like.)

106
00:06:49,770 --> 00:06:51,599
You keep trying to find the perfect angle to look cool.

107
00:06:51,600 --> 00:06:53,640
It's because I can't see anything from here.

108
00:06:54,070 --> 00:06:55,839
Are we really going horseback riding today?

109
00:06:55,840 --> 00:06:57,169
Kwang Soo, we came all the way to Jeju.

110
00:06:57,170 --> 00:06:58,880
Shouldn't we make at least this much effort?

111
00:07:00,110 --> 00:07:02,650
Could you even board a plane dressed like that?

112
00:07:03,080 --> 00:07:04,750
Can you even board when you look this suspicious?

113
00:07:06,780 --> 00:07:11,620
(GBRB: Farm Operation - Go Go Farm)

114
00:07:11,890 --> 00:07:14,959
Even if you know about it, you probably have a rough idea.

115
00:07:14,960 --> 00:07:16,260
- You don't know the details.
- Right.

116
00:07:16,330 --> 00:07:17,529
The CEO will personally explain...

117
00:07:17,530 --> 00:07:19,099
what you'll be doing this season.

118
00:07:19,100 --> 00:07:20,459
- That's probably better...
- You mean, CEO Ko?

119
00:07:20,460 --> 00:07:21,969
- Is CEO Ko coming?
- Yes.

120
00:07:21,970 --> 00:07:24,229
- He's also the CEO.
- Right.

121
00:07:24,230 --> 00:07:26,000
Is that still valid?

122
00:07:26,700 --> 00:07:27,809
- Still?
- Of course.

123
00:07:27,810 --> 00:07:29,469
- Isn't it over?
- What do you mean?

124
00:07:29,470 --> 00:07:30,770
Since when is it over?

125
00:07:30,870 --> 00:07:31,910
Hello, sir.

126
00:07:32,140 --> 00:07:33,309
Hello.

127
00:07:33,310 --> 00:07:34,579
- Hello.
- Hello.

128
00:07:34,580 --> 00:07:35,809
CEO Ko.

129
00:07:35,810 --> 00:07:37,980
- It's been a long time.
- Yes, it's been a while.

130
00:07:38,020 --> 00:07:39,549
Could you explain...

131
00:07:39,550 --> 00:07:41,689
what KKPP staff are...

132
00:07:41,690 --> 00:07:42,719
supposed to be doing...

133
00:07:42,720 --> 00:07:44,419
- this season?
- Okay.

134
00:07:44,420 --> 00:07:45,420
I'm sorry, Woo Bin,

135
00:07:45,421 --> 00:07:46,659
- but can we switch seats?
- Why?

136
00:07:46,660 --> 00:07:48,259
- I need to face the CEO.
- I see.

137
00:07:48,260 --> 00:07:50,459
(The presence of the CEO at the 3-person company is strong.)

138
00:07:50,460 --> 00:07:51,630
You're making me uncomfortable.

139
00:07:51,830 --> 00:07:53,930
(The seating gets arranged.)

140
00:07:54,160 --> 00:07:57,229
You know how people have a resident registration certificate?

141
00:07:57,230 --> 00:07:58,669
Have you heard of resident registration certificate?

142
00:07:58,670 --> 00:08:00,399
- Resident registration card...
- Of course I know what it is.

143
00:08:00,400 --> 00:08:01,409
and certificate.

144
00:08:01,410 --> 00:08:02,740
What kind of question is that?

145
00:08:02,840 --> 00:08:04,880
- I'm 42 years old.
- Excuse me.

146
00:08:05,310 --> 00:08:07,379
Please show respect to our CEO.

147
00:08:07,380 --> 00:08:10,179
Companies also have a certificate like that.

148
00:08:10,180 --> 00:08:11,619
Corporate registration certificate.

149
00:08:11,620 --> 00:08:13,079
Let me show you this.

150
00:08:13,080 --> 00:08:15,249
- Is this your registration?
- This is egg is coming's...

151
00:08:15,250 --> 00:08:17,319
- Take a look here.
- corporate registration.

152
00:08:17,320 --> 00:08:19,690
Take a look at number 20.

153
00:08:19,790 --> 00:08:21,659
- Take a look at number 20.
- Okay.

154
00:08:21,660 --> 00:08:22,660
- Is it really true?
- Yes.

155
00:08:22,661 --> 00:08:24,059
Yes, it's true.

156
00:08:24,060 --> 00:08:26,229
This was issued by the court.

157
00:08:26,230 --> 00:08:27,230
It's true.

158
00:08:27,231 --> 00:08:29,369
You can't just make this up.

159
00:08:29,370 --> 00:08:31,899
It says "poultry farming and distribution related to poultry."

160
00:08:31,900 --> 00:08:33,700
Yes, I'm not making this up.

161
00:08:34,910 --> 00:08:35,910
- This...
- What is...

162
00:08:36,310 --> 00:08:37,640
- Seriously?
- Yes.

163
00:08:38,210 --> 00:08:41,039
It's what you registered when you founded the company.

164
00:08:41,040 --> 00:08:42,080
That's right.

165
00:08:42,450 --> 00:08:43,450
- KKPP...
- Yes.

166
00:08:43,650 --> 00:08:46,480
When you establish a company,

167
00:08:46,980 --> 00:08:48,949
you're told to include...

168
00:08:48,950 --> 00:08:51,719
all possible business areas in case you want to expand later.

169
00:08:51,720 --> 00:08:52,819
- Right.
- I see.

170
00:08:52,820 --> 00:08:54,660
One of the items we wrote was...

171
00:08:55,560 --> 00:08:57,689
poultry farming.

172
00:08:57,690 --> 00:08:59,359
- Hold on a second.
- Yes?

173
00:08:59,360 --> 00:09:01,229
You planned to farm poultry?

174
00:09:01,230 --> 00:09:02,230
Yes.

175
00:09:02,630 --> 00:09:04,430
Is that why you're called egg is coming?

176
00:09:04,530 --> 00:09:07,400
We named it egg is coming.

177
00:09:07,700 --> 00:09:09,509
If we don't do anything related to poultry,

178
00:09:09,510 --> 00:09:11,409
it'd feel a bit insincere.

179
00:09:11,410 --> 00:09:12,710
That's how the conversation came up.

180
00:09:12,810 --> 00:09:14,379
- In reality...
- After naming it?

181
00:09:14,380 --> 00:09:15,879
- I'm being serious.
- It's really true.

182
00:09:15,880 --> 00:09:17,109
- Seriously?
- Yes.

183
00:09:17,110 --> 00:09:21,419
We at egg is coming had a dream.

184
00:09:21,420 --> 00:09:25,059
When we make shows like "Three Meals A Day,"

185
00:09:25,060 --> 00:09:26,389
"GBRB," or "Jinny's Kitchen,"

186
00:09:26,390 --> 00:09:29,189
we didn't want them to be just TV programs.

187
00:09:29,190 --> 00:09:30,459
We wanted them to exist in real life.

188
00:09:30,460 --> 00:09:34,259
So we'd grow crops and harvest vegetables.

189
00:09:34,260 --> 00:09:36,030
When the vegetables are harvested,

190
00:09:36,130 --> 00:09:38,700
someone like Kyung Soo would cook them.

191
00:09:38,970 --> 00:09:40,769
If we have a ranch,

192
00:09:40,770 --> 00:09:42,040
we'd raise cows and chickens.

193
00:09:42,410 --> 00:09:44,910
Using milk from the cows,

194
00:09:45,010 --> 00:09:46,609
we'd make ice cream...

195
00:09:46,610 --> 00:09:48,310
or shaved ice.

196
00:09:48,680 --> 00:09:50,150
That's what we hoped.

197
00:09:50,780 --> 00:09:53,880
We dreamed of creating something like a theme park.

198
00:09:54,650 --> 00:09:56,950
But why?

199
00:09:57,220 --> 00:10:00,390
I mean, why was that your dream?

200
00:10:00,490 --> 00:10:01,660
I really want to know.

201
00:10:01,960 --> 00:10:04,529
Do you remember our preliminary meeting last year?

202
00:10:04,530 --> 00:10:06,799
When we asked you to brief us...

203
00:10:06,800 --> 00:10:08,169
on what you wanted to do,

204
00:10:08,170 --> 00:10:10,330
what did CEO Kwang Soo say?

205
00:10:10,700 --> 00:10:11,740
What did you say?

206
00:10:12,740 --> 00:10:14,539
- I don't know.
- What did you say back then?

207
00:10:14,540 --> 00:10:16,269
He wanted to do something with animals.

208
00:10:16,270 --> 00:10:18,509
Right. I think I remember him saying that.

209
00:10:18,510 --> 00:10:19,579
- Maybe you meant...
- He wanted...

210
00:10:19,580 --> 00:10:21,610
doing something with dogs or cats.

211
00:10:22,580 --> 00:10:25,749
He said that he wanted to raise a parrot on his shoulder.

212
00:10:25,750 --> 00:10:27,279
I do like all animals.

213
00:10:27,280 --> 00:10:28,549
I like all animals.

214
00:10:28,550 --> 00:10:30,489
That's when we had the idea.

215
00:10:30,490 --> 00:10:32,789
The dream we had forgotten.

216
00:10:32,790 --> 00:10:34,219
The dream of livestock farming.

217
00:10:34,220 --> 00:10:36,060
- Through KKPP...
- We said that we wanted to do it.

218
00:10:36,160 --> 00:10:37,730
We did say that we wanted to do it.

219
00:10:38,330 --> 00:10:40,160
You grew crops.

220
00:10:40,260 --> 00:10:42,170
You also ran a restaurant.

221
00:10:43,170 --> 00:10:44,769
To build international experience,

222
00:10:44,770 --> 00:10:45,800
you even went abroad for training.

223
00:10:46,140 --> 00:10:49,609
We invested a huge amount of money in you.

224
00:10:49,610 --> 00:10:50,670
I know.

225
00:10:50,870 --> 00:10:53,680
What we haven't done yet is livestock.

226
00:10:54,140 --> 00:10:56,009
Woo Bin might like it the most.

227
00:10:56,010 --> 00:10:57,010
- Me?
- Yes.

228
00:10:57,780 --> 00:10:58,820
How so?

229
00:10:59,920 --> 00:11:03,190
Woo Bin, your favorite thing is protein.

230
00:11:03,590 --> 00:11:06,119
Are you telling him to raise chickens and eat them?

231
00:11:06,120 --> 00:11:07,989
No, not at all.

232
00:11:07,990 --> 00:11:08,990
Are you telling us to eat chicken breasts?

233
00:11:08,991 --> 00:11:10,929
No, there are also eggs...

234
00:11:10,930 --> 00:11:12,960
and milk.

235
00:11:13,060 --> 00:11:14,899
You guys like animals, don't you?

236
00:11:14,900 --> 00:11:16,530
- I do.
- I do, but...

237
00:11:17,170 --> 00:11:18,700
You'll have a great time.

238
00:11:18,970 --> 00:11:21,769
Among our partner companies, we selected two sites.

239
00:11:21,770 --> 00:11:24,710
We signed MOUs with them for a technical training program.

240
00:11:25,010 --> 00:11:26,610
- The first one is...
- Excuse me.

241
00:11:26,880 --> 00:11:29,750
If you get too serious, we might not understand you.

242
00:11:29,850 --> 00:11:31,549
If we're going into livestock farming,

243
00:11:31,550 --> 00:11:34,379
we figured we needed some expertise.

244
00:11:34,380 --> 00:11:36,150
- We agreed to send three people...
- Right.

245
00:11:36,420 --> 00:11:39,359
to learn the expertise.

246
00:11:39,360 --> 00:11:43,029
We made an agreement to make such a TV show.

247
00:11:43,030 --> 00:11:44,030
(This is what we call "technical training.")

248
00:11:44,031 --> 00:11:45,629
- Where will it take place?
- Where?

249
00:11:45,630 --> 00:11:48,729
One is at a dairy farm.

250
00:11:48,730 --> 00:11:49,730
What?

251
00:11:49,731 --> 00:11:51,770
The other is at a horse ranch.

252
00:11:53,000 --> 00:11:54,500
So we're going to milk cows?

253
00:11:56,410 --> 00:11:57,910
No, milking cows...

254
00:11:58,210 --> 00:11:59,810
It's gotten way out of hand.

255
00:11:59,910 --> 00:12:01,450
CEO Ko's dream is too big.

256
00:12:03,480 --> 00:12:05,779
How would my learning...

257
00:12:05,780 --> 00:12:08,490
of milking cows help KKPP's development?

258
00:12:09,150 --> 00:12:11,560
I'm not sure at this point.

259
00:12:11,760 --> 00:12:14,490
Isn't it done with machines these days?

260
00:12:14,860 --> 00:12:16,390
We don't milk cows by hand anymore.

261
00:12:16,690 --> 00:12:17,690
Or do we?

262
00:12:18,260 --> 00:12:19,300
I'm not sure.

263
00:12:19,630 --> 00:12:21,600
Anyway, I'll do my best.

264
00:12:23,870 --> 00:12:25,169
(They arrive on Jeju Island.)

265
00:12:25,170 --> 00:12:26,399
Kwang Soo, get in from this side.

266
00:12:26,400 --> 00:12:27,440
Okay.

267
00:12:29,570 --> 00:12:31,240
Isn't it still sunny in Seoul?

268
00:12:31,840 --> 00:12:33,639
I think it's sunny there.

269
00:12:33,640 --> 00:12:35,149
Could the weather be so different here?

