803
00:31:32,650 --> 00:31:36,820
(At that time, a gigantic something approaches from afar.)

804
00:31:40,890 --> 00:31:42,120
(Kyung Soo is surprised.)

805
00:31:42,590 --> 00:31:44,589
It looks a bit like "Mad Max."

806
00:31:44,590 --> 00:31:46,059
You're right. It's cool.

807
00:31:46,060 --> 00:31:47,060
It's cool.

808
00:31:48,230 --> 00:31:49,870
(Woo Bin is impressed.)

809
00:31:52,000 --> 00:31:53,440
It's cool.

810
00:31:59,780 --> 00:32:01,609
- That's how they do it.
- They drag it.

811
00:32:01,610 --> 00:32:04,450
(The dragged cow dung is stored in a compost shed.)

812
00:32:06,380 --> 00:32:09,179
It's done so neatly.

813
00:32:09,180 --> 00:32:10,189
(Where the tractor passed is cleaned neatly.)

814
00:32:10,190 --> 00:32:12,349
- This is so good.
- I know, right?

815
00:32:12,350 --> 00:32:13,960
(But no matter how good of a tractor it is,)

816
00:32:14,760 --> 00:32:17,830
(it can't clean the cow dung on the edge.)

817
00:32:19,160 --> 00:32:20,229
Come here.

818
00:32:20,230 --> 00:32:21,500
(Which means, the trainees have to clean it.)

819
00:32:22,730 --> 00:32:24,500
Stepping on it feels so...

820
00:32:25,070 --> 00:32:26,500
- It's really dung.
- So this is really dung.

821
00:32:27,570 --> 00:32:29,000
All of this is dung.

822
00:32:29,270 --> 00:32:31,940
Dung and hay mixed, I think.

823
00:32:33,910 --> 00:32:35,740
CEO Lee, push it using that.

824
00:32:36,080 --> 00:32:37,650
- Push with this?
- Yes, push it.

825
00:32:39,350 --> 00:32:40,949
All the way to there.

826
00:32:40,950 --> 00:32:41,979
Like that.

827
00:32:41,980 --> 00:32:44,750
(There are two big steps to cleaning cow dung.)

828
00:32:46,060 --> 00:32:47,319
(1. Break hard cow dung using a rake.)

829
00:32:47,320 --> 00:32:49,930
- You scrape it out like this.
- Yes.

830
00:32:51,530 --> 00:32:53,559
You push it to the side here.

831
00:32:53,560 --> 00:32:57,500
(2. Push the broken cow dung to the compost shed.)

832
00:32:59,340 --> 00:33:05,570
(Trainee Kyung Soo breaks the cow dung himself.)

833
00:33:06,680 --> 00:33:08,840
Guys, it's heavy!

834
00:33:08,940 --> 00:33:10,580
It's so heavy.

835
00:33:11,580 --> 00:33:13,379
It's hard to scoop it.

836
00:33:13,380 --> 00:33:14,649
It isn't easy.

837
00:33:14,650 --> 00:33:16,390
It's different from what I thought.

838
00:33:17,220 --> 00:33:18,220
(Woo Bin struggles.)

839
00:33:18,950 --> 00:33:20,090
This is hard.

840
00:33:21,290 --> 00:33:23,289
- This is...
- It's heavier than I thought.

841
00:33:23,290 --> 00:33:24,290
Darn it.

842
00:33:25,890 --> 00:33:27,400
It's different from what I thought.

843
00:33:30,230 --> 00:33:33,740
(Cleaning cow dung seems to be harder than they thought.)

844
00:33:36,310 --> 00:33:39,510
(Trainee Kwang Soo looks serious.)

845
00:33:41,640 --> 00:33:43,380
(Kyung Soo laughing)

846
00:33:43,950 --> 00:33:45,850
(Kyung Soo laughing)

847
00:33:47,050 --> 00:33:48,050
Why?

848
00:33:48,720 --> 00:33:50,889
- Look at him.
- What?

849
00:33:50,890 --> 00:33:52,120
He has a weak stomach.

850
00:33:52,860 --> 00:33:55,060
(Kyung Soo laughing)

851
00:33:56,660 --> 00:33:58,030
Kwang Soo, just do it.

852
00:34:01,160 --> 00:34:03,130
I've never smelled something like this before.

853
00:34:04,600 --> 00:34:05,600
That...

854
00:34:06,900 --> 00:34:08,470
Since you dig it around...

855
00:34:11,240 --> 00:34:12,940
It's fine if you leave it alone.

856
00:34:13,740 --> 00:34:14,740
That...

857
00:34:15,010 --> 00:34:16,880
You need to keep doing it.

858
00:34:17,510 --> 00:34:18,980
Go get some fresh air.

859
00:34:20,420 --> 00:34:21,650
I'll go have a quick meeting.

860
00:34:23,850 --> 00:34:25,819
(Kwang Soo sighs.)

861
00:34:25,820 --> 00:34:28,720
(We're watching you.)

862
00:34:35,930 --> 00:34:36,930
(Snap)

863
00:34:37,900 --> 00:34:38,930
- What?
- Goodness.

864
00:34:40,100 --> 00:34:41,399
(Kwang Soo sighs.)

865
00:34:41,400 --> 00:34:42,470
Sir!

866
00:34:42,770 --> 00:34:44,209
- No.
- Mr. Kkalloo!

867
00:34:44,210 --> 00:34:46,939
- No.
- He broke it.

868
00:34:46,940 --> 00:34:47,940
He broke it?

869
00:34:47,941 --> 00:34:49,110
- Kyung Soo broke it.
- I didn't.

870
00:34:50,180 --> 00:34:51,510
- He...
- I didn't break it.

871
00:34:53,050 --> 00:34:54,249
I'm not telling on him.

872
00:34:54,250 --> 00:34:56,390
When you evaluate us later on, can you...

873
00:34:57,220 --> 00:34:59,760
You know, vandalism and so on.

874
00:35:01,220 --> 00:35:02,489
- Don't forget it.
- Okay.

875
00:35:02,490 --> 00:35:03,759
Doh Kyung Soo...

876
00:35:03,760 --> 00:35:04,889
(Don't forget, "Doh Kyung Soo, vandalism.")

877
00:35:04,890 --> 00:35:05,960
He broke one.

878
00:35:08,900 --> 00:35:13,470
(They focus on the training.)

879
00:35:24,850 --> 00:35:27,080
Let's hold two each, stand in one line, and push.

880
00:35:27,120 --> 00:35:28,180
Let's try it.

881
00:35:29,380 --> 00:35:31,720
- From there.
- You can't control it.

882
00:35:32,320 --> 00:35:33,320
You can't do it.

883
00:35:33,321 --> 00:35:34,590
(Times 2 strategy fails.)

884
00:35:40,660 --> 00:35:41,660
(Woo Bin grunts.)

885
00:35:44,330 --> 00:35:46,170
This is rather fun.

886
00:35:47,800 --> 00:35:50,210
(Not for me.)

887
00:35:54,010 --> 00:35:57,680
(Current time: 4:30pm, 1 hour 30 minutes have passed.)

888
00:35:58,810 --> 00:36:00,380
It's a lot more than I thought.

889
00:36:00,880 --> 00:36:03,820
(There's still so much more left to clean.)

890
00:36:05,220 --> 00:36:06,260
Today...

891
00:36:07,820 --> 00:36:09,660
I'll keep pooping in my dream.

892
00:36:10,490 --> 00:36:11,490
In my dream...

893
00:36:12,790 --> 00:36:15,460
You won't understand from watching the show.

894
00:36:16,630 --> 00:36:18,670
Wasn't our show supposed to be fun to watch while eating?

895
00:36:19,640 --> 00:36:22,069
All they'll see is us cleaning poop.

896
00:36:22,070 --> 00:36:23,240
(The meal-friendly show which shows poop all the time)

897
00:36:24,410 --> 00:36:25,440
But...

898
00:36:26,680 --> 00:36:28,279
Why are you stepping on the...

899
00:36:28,280 --> 00:36:29,480
Hey, move.

900
00:36:30,550 --> 00:36:32,809
How could you step on it? I have to break it up again.

901
00:36:32,810 --> 00:36:34,679
(The production staff stepped on the broken-up cattle manure.)

902
00:36:34,680 --> 00:36:35,750
Why...

903
00:36:37,290 --> 00:36:38,890
It was done, you know?

904
00:36:42,190 --> 00:36:44,130
It's... Hey.

905
00:36:44,560 --> 00:36:45,830
Seriously.

906
00:36:46,630 --> 00:36:47,829
Why are you stepping in there?

907
00:36:47,830 --> 00:36:49,530
To take what? Footage of the poop?

908
00:36:49,630 --> 00:36:51,630
What are you trying to film? We're all here, aren't we?

909
00:36:52,870 --> 00:36:53,969
Why do you keep stepping on it?

910
00:36:53,970 --> 00:36:55,970
You keep stepping on it after I break it up.

911
00:36:59,710 --> 00:37:01,580
Why clean it up when they'll poop again?

912
00:37:02,440 --> 00:37:03,449
(Furious about the endless poop)

913
00:37:03,450 --> 00:37:04,450
Won't it be...

914
00:37:05,310 --> 00:37:06,720
a field of poop again when we return later?

915
00:37:08,080 --> 00:37:11,350
(That's what we do.)

916
00:37:11,890 --> 00:37:13,359
I'm just curious.

917
00:37:13,360 --> 00:37:15,289
Couldn't it have done a more thorough job?

918
00:37:15,290 --> 00:37:17,460
Is that really the best it could do?

919
00:37:18,360 --> 00:37:21,559
I see places where the tractor can fit through.

920
00:37:21,560 --> 00:37:22,560
(There's a lot left even after using the tractor.)

921
00:37:23,170 --> 00:37:25,529
(They get to it either way.)

922
00:37:25,530 --> 00:37:26,570
Careful of your back.

923
00:37:29,470 --> 00:37:30,570
(Surprised)

924
00:37:31,240 --> 00:37:34,410
Oh, no. That was close. Are you okay?

925
00:37:35,180 --> 00:37:36,350
This is dangerous.

926
00:37:37,950 --> 00:37:40,350
(Wiping himself off)

927
00:37:40,450 --> 00:37:42,080
(Laughing)

928
00:37:43,090 --> 00:37:44,320
My zipper has poop on it.

929
00:37:46,420 --> 00:37:47,460
I'm sorry.

930
00:37:49,630 --> 00:37:51,190
- Let's get going.
- Okay.

931
00:37:52,730 --> 00:37:54,199
It's dangerous to throw it behind.

932
00:37:54,200 --> 00:37:55,330
I should watch where I throw it.

933
00:37:57,770 --> 00:38:00,100
(He's more cautious about where he's throwing it.)

934
00:38:01,340 --> 00:38:03,610
(Stopping)

935
00:38:04,110 --> 00:38:05,639
I'm watching where I'm throwing it.

936
00:38:05,640 --> 00:38:06,809
Watch where you throw it, for real.

937
00:38:06,810 --> 00:38:08,610
Okay. I'm watching.

938
00:38:09,540 --> 00:38:10,979
For real, watch where you throw it.

939
00:38:10,980 --> 00:38:12,710
For real, okay?

940
00:38:13,520 --> 00:38:15,120
I can let it slide the first time.

941
00:38:15,520 --> 00:38:17,149
(But not the second.)

942
00:38:17,150 --> 00:38:18,390
For real, watch where you throw it.

943
00:38:22,320 --> 00:38:23,760
(Mooing)

944
00:38:23,930 --> 00:38:24,960
What's going on?

945
00:38:26,560 --> 00:38:28,130
What could that be?

946
00:38:28,230 --> 00:38:29,630
- What?
- Them suddenly crying.

947
00:38:30,230 --> 00:38:31,970
All the cows are mooing together.

948
00:38:32,800 --> 00:38:34,769
- Right? They were quiet until now.
- True.

949
00:38:34,770 --> 00:38:36,140
Is it time for something?

950
00:38:37,470 --> 00:38:38,539
Are they asking for food?

951
00:38:38,540 --> 00:38:40,779
Sir, why are the cows suddenly mooing?

952
00:38:40,780 --> 00:38:41,979
Are they asking for food?

953
00:38:41,980 --> 00:38:44,609
Boss, why are the cows suddenly mooing?

954
00:38:44,610 --> 00:38:45,679
Their food is here.

955
00:38:45,680 --> 00:38:46,920
Where?

956
00:38:47,420 --> 00:38:48,420
Because of the food?

957
00:38:50,950 --> 00:38:52,019
- Over there.
- Their food is here.

958
00:38:52,020 --> 00:38:53,419
Those must be milk.

959
00:38:53,420 --> 00:38:54,420
(5pm: Dinner time for the calves)

960
00:38:55,120 --> 00:38:56,330
Are they mooing because of the smell?

961
00:38:56,430 --> 00:38:58,289
No, it's because of the sound of the wheels.

962
00:38:58,290 --> 00:39:00,329
- The sound?
- The rattling sound.

963
00:39:00,330 --> 00:39:01,929
- How adorable.
- They're eating.

964
00:39:01,930 --> 00:39:03,469
Gosh, they're cute.

965
00:39:03,470 --> 00:39:05,000
(Leaving the workplace after hearing the calves are eating)

966
00:39:05,600 --> 00:39:06,970
They're all looking this way.

967
00:39:12,070 --> 00:39:13,239
They're just like puppies.

968
00:39:13,240 --> 00:39:15,310
- True.
- "Give me food."

969
00:39:17,410 --> 00:39:18,410
How do you feed them?

970
00:39:18,410 --> 00:39:19,410
Milk.

971
00:39:19,980 --> 00:39:21,520
So it's their mother's milk.

972
00:39:21,620 --> 00:39:22,850
Yes, pour it all in.

973
00:39:23,850 --> 00:39:25,549
- It's warm.
- You're right.

974
00:39:25,550 --> 00:39:26,590
- Is it warm?
- Yes.

975
00:39:27,390 --> 00:39:28,789
It's really warm.

976
00:39:28,790 --> 00:39:30,090
It was milked earlier today.

977
00:39:30,360 --> 00:39:31,689
Smell it. It's nice.

978
00:39:31,690 --> 00:39:32,730
I know, right?

979
00:39:35,600 --> 00:39:36,970
It smells like butter. Oh, my.

980
00:39:37,830 --> 00:39:39,430
- Like this?
- Yes.

981
00:39:40,340 --> 00:39:41,670
- Do I pour it in here?
- Yes.

982
00:39:42,100 --> 00:39:43,870
Look at them from the side.

983
00:39:45,270 --> 00:39:48,609
(The calves are gathered in front of the milk bucket.)

984
00:39:48,610 --> 00:39:50,009
It's steaming.

985
00:39:50,010 --> 00:39:51,610
- They're sucking on it fast.
- It's steaming.

986
00:39:54,720 --> 00:39:55,720
Look over here, Kwang Soo.

987
00:39:56,080 --> 00:39:57,250
Look at them suck on it.

988
00:39:58,090 --> 00:39:59,420
It's so cute.

989
00:40:01,620 --> 00:40:03,060
Why are they this adorable?

990
00:40:03,260 --> 00:40:06,660
(The smile of Cow Daddy)

991
00:40:08,030 --> 00:40:09,360
Aren't they cute?

992
00:40:10,830 --> 00:40:12,570
They're like puppies.

993
00:40:16,270 --> 00:40:17,840
You can hear them sucking.

994
00:40:23,150 --> 00:40:25,449
This is the kind of hands-on farm experience I had in mind.

995
00:40:25,450 --> 00:40:26,450
For real.

996
00:40:27,480 --> 00:40:28,480
Over here.

997
00:40:28,481 --> 00:40:29,749
(Laughing)

998
00:40:29,750 --> 00:40:30,889
It's a baby bowl.

999
00:40:30,890 --> 00:40:32,250
(Even the small bowl makes them laugh.)

1000
00:40:33,620 --> 00:40:34,989
Bottle-feeding?

1001
00:40:34,990 --> 00:40:36,389
(Even the calf drinking milk makes them happy.)

1002
00:40:36,390 --> 00:40:37,430
(Laughing)

1003
00:40:39,190 --> 00:40:40,529
It was born yesterday.

1004
00:40:40,530 --> 00:40:42,300
- Really?
- Yes.

1005
00:40:42,600 --> 00:40:44,799
How was it born yesterday?

1006
00:40:44,800 --> 00:40:46,900
- It was born yesterday.
- I know, right?

1007
00:40:47,840 --> 00:40:48,900
Is it good?

1008
00:40:49,440 --> 00:40:52,770
(Feeding colostrum to the calf born yesterday)

1009
00:40:53,380 --> 00:40:54,780
It's drinking the milk fast.

1010
00:40:55,610 --> 00:40:57,050
- It's empty.
- It's already empty.

1011
00:40:59,280 --> 00:41:01,320
Look at its eyes. It's scary.

1012
00:41:02,420 --> 00:41:03,420
It's scared of losing the bottle.

1013
00:41:03,550 --> 00:41:05,920
All finished. The milk is gone now.

1014
00:41:07,490 --> 00:41:09,090
(Burping)

1015
00:41:09,190 --> 00:41:10,260
It just burped.

1016
00:41:11,460 --> 00:41:12,490
Hey, it burped.

1017
00:41:12,590 --> 00:41:13,830
- For real?
- Yes.

1018
00:41:14,660 --> 00:41:17,229
CEO Lee, how about giving it a name?

1019
00:41:17,230 --> 00:41:18,300
- Which one?
- This one here.

1020
00:41:18,600 --> 00:41:20,039
Give it a name, CEO Lee.

1021
00:41:20,040 --> 00:41:21,339
(Born 2 days ago, born 10 days ago)

1022
00:41:21,340 --> 00:41:22,540
(Asked to give the calves a name)

1023
00:41:22,900 --> 00:41:26,039
You could name them according to the weather,

1024
00:41:26,040 --> 00:41:27,040
- Right.
- or whatever you prefer.

1025
00:41:27,041 --> 00:41:28,679
- How's Farmfarm?
- Farmfarm?

1026
00:41:28,680 --> 00:41:29,780
(Mooing)

1027
00:41:29,910 --> 00:41:31,149
- Farmfarm?
- We've got two calves.

1028
00:41:31,150 --> 00:41:32,609
Name that one too.

1029
00:41:32,610 --> 00:41:33,819
- Gogo for one.
- Okay.

1030
00:41:33,820 --> 00:41:34,979
- Gogo and Farmfarm.
- Got it.

1031
00:41:34,980 --> 00:41:36,050
Nice.

1032
00:41:36,820 --> 00:41:37,989
She's the older one.

1033
00:41:37,990 --> 00:41:39,589
- The older one is Gogo.
- Older sister is Gogo.

1034
00:41:39,590 --> 00:41:41,359
- The younger one is Farmfarm.
- Farmfarm.

1035
00:41:41,360 --> 00:41:42,519
Farmfarm. Gogo and Farmfarm.

1036
00:41:42,520 --> 00:41:44,860
- Farmfarm.
- Hey, Farmfarm.

1037
00:41:46,030 --> 00:41:49,299
(Personally writing down the names on the ear tags)

1038
00:41:49,300 --> 00:41:51,399
(Farmfarm)

1039
00:41:51,400 --> 00:41:53,300
Naming them is such an honor.

1040
00:41:54,740 --> 00:41:56,399
(The newly born calves have names now.)

1041
00:41:56,400 --> 00:41:58,140
(Gogo, the 10-day-old older sister)

1042
00:41:59,070 --> 00:42:02,080
(Farmfarm, the 2-day-old younger sister)

1043
00:42:02,410 --> 00:42:03,510
(The trainees got sidetracked.)

1044
00:42:04,250 --> 00:42:05,250
Wait.

1045
00:42:05,251 --> 00:42:07,680
(The trainees got sidetracked.)

1046
00:42:08,250 --> 00:42:09,419
Even so, food comes first.

1047
00:42:09,420 --> 00:42:10,420
- Is that so?
- Yes.

1048
00:42:10,520 --> 00:42:11,989
They must be fed first.

1049
00:42:11,990 --> 00:42:13,990
(As expected, food comes first for K-Cow Daddy.)

1050
00:42:14,120 --> 00:42:15,120
But I'm not sure...

1051
00:42:16,360 --> 00:42:17,830
if they'll be able to finish it.

1052
00:42:18,090 --> 00:42:19,130
- Right?
- Yes.

1053
00:42:20,000 --> 00:42:21,430
Let's go clean up the poop, Kwang Soo.

1054
00:42:24,100 --> 00:42:26,100
Gosh, it's getting dark.

1055
00:42:26,230 --> 00:42:27,470
Kwang Soo, we should hurry.

1056
00:42:28,870 --> 00:42:30,810
"Gosh, it's getting dark."

1057
00:42:33,480 --> 00:42:34,980
He's the sly type.

1058
00:42:37,350 --> 00:42:38,549
(Remaining tasks: Clean poop,)

1059
00:42:38,550 --> 00:42:39,879
(spread sawdust, bring in the juvenile cows)

1060
00:42:39,880 --> 00:42:42,679
Kwang Soo, if we move the poop to the center,

1061
00:42:42,680 --> 00:42:44,550
the tractor can shove it.

1062
00:42:44,850 --> 00:42:45,920
You're right.

1063
00:42:46,120 --> 00:42:49,859
Push them to this side, and the tractor can do the rest.

1064
00:42:49,860 --> 00:42:51,490
(Both suggest using the tractor.)

1065
00:42:51,890 --> 00:42:53,559
We can spread the poop to both sides.

1066
00:42:53,560 --> 00:42:54,560
- Right.
- Okay.

1067
00:42:55,100 --> 00:43:00,570
(Starting Round 2 of breaking the center manure)

1068
00:43:02,770 --> 00:43:05,810
(Looking like farmers plowing a field)

1069
00:43:07,180 --> 00:43:08,280
Gosh, this one's huge.

1070
00:43:11,450 --> 00:43:13,750
Woo Bin, can't you see the layers of the poop?

1071
00:43:13,980 --> 00:43:15,519
- This...
- Really old poop.

1072
00:43:15,520 --> 00:43:17,150
- Can you see the buildup of poop?
- Totally.

1073
00:43:18,120 --> 00:43:20,060
These must have been here since the Stone Age.

1074
00:43:21,360 --> 00:43:23,730
Judging by the amount of gas...

1075
00:43:25,090 --> 00:43:27,200
Sir, these poops must've been here for a while.

1076
00:43:27,530 --> 00:43:28,530
Yes.

1077
00:43:30,200 --> 00:43:31,300
They've been there for a while.

1078
00:43:32,270 --> 00:43:33,300
What's with that?

1079
00:43:35,540 --> 00:43:38,010
It's clean around the pillars now.

1080
00:43:38,770 --> 00:43:40,839
(The areas around the pillars are clean.)

1081
00:43:40,840 --> 00:43:42,940
- This feels nice.
- Yes.

1082
00:43:43,040 --> 00:43:45,950
If only the weather were great, you know?

1083
00:43:46,720 --> 00:43:48,119
Here it comes again.

1084
00:43:48,120 --> 00:43:50,090
(Using the tractor)

1085
00:43:50,390 --> 00:43:52,019
Kwang Soo, look at how clean the pillars are.

1086
00:43:52,020 --> 00:43:53,020
For real.

1087
00:43:53,250 --> 00:43:55,560
(Amazed)

1088
00:44:00,800 --> 00:44:03,630
(Smiling brightly)

1089
00:44:04,870 --> 00:44:05,870
If I were a cow,

1090
00:44:05,871 --> 00:44:07,600
I'd cry looking at this scene.

1091
00:44:08,540 --> 00:44:09,600
I'm serious.

1092
00:44:10,770 --> 00:44:12,469
Wasn't there a show, fixing people's houses?

1093
00:44:12,470 --> 00:44:14,209
- Yes.
- What was it again?

1094
00:44:14,210 --> 00:44:16,779
- "Love House." - That's the one.

1095
00:44:16,780 --> 00:44:17,950
(Back in the day home theme)

1096
00:44:18,150 --> 00:44:20,080
We should bring the cow blindfolded.

1097
00:44:20,980 --> 00:44:22,650
"Take the blindfold off."

1098
00:44:22,820 --> 00:44:23,820
"Oh, my!"

1099
00:44:24,890 --> 00:44:27,259
I feel happy now that the floor is clean.

1100
00:44:27,260 --> 00:44:28,320
Totally.

1101
00:44:28,960 --> 00:44:29,960
(In awe)

1102
00:44:29,961 --> 00:44:31,159
It's squeaky clean now.

1103
00:44:31,160 --> 00:44:33,460
(Now that the cattle shed is clean)

1104
00:44:34,560 --> 00:44:35,860
(Surprised)

1105
00:44:36,000 --> 00:44:37,429
It sort of looks like a hive.

1106
00:44:37,430 --> 00:44:38,430
Right?

1107
00:44:38,900 --> 00:44:39,929
- Really.
- CEO Lee,

1108
00:44:39,930 --> 00:44:41,000
the stress from cleaning poop.

1109
00:44:42,170 --> 00:44:43,709
(How to relieve the stress from cleaning the manure)

1110
00:44:43,710 --> 00:44:45,010
- There.
- Do we just throw it in there?

1111
00:44:47,080 --> 00:44:49,410
(Slamming down)

1112
00:44:53,380 --> 00:44:54,949
(Ranch tip:)

1113
00:44:54,950 --> 00:44:57,650
(Spread sawdust on the shed floor to prevent slipping on cattle manure)

1114
00:44:58,220 --> 00:44:59,889
Woo Bin must be quite upset.

1115
00:44:59,890 --> 00:45:01,759
(Laughing)

1116
00:45:01,760 --> 00:45:04,160
Looking at the sawdust spread apart is making my day.

1117
00:45:05,090 --> 00:45:06,160
It's pretty.

1118
00:45:07,530 --> 00:45:09,260
Right? The color is pretty.

1119
00:45:11,670 --> 00:45:12,870
Why is it so hard?

1120
00:45:14,440 --> 00:45:17,170
(So that the resident cows live comfortably)

1121
00:45:17,870 --> 00:45:19,840
(Breaking up the sawdust)

1122
00:45:20,540 --> 00:45:21,810
Isn't this fun, Kwang Soo?

1123
00:45:22,040 --> 00:45:23,810
- It's making me happy.
- Same here.

1124
00:45:24,650 --> 00:45:26,280
Well done.

1125
00:45:27,280 --> 00:45:29,720
(The trainees get praised.)

1126
00:45:29,820 --> 00:45:30,820
The cows...

1127
00:45:31,190 --> 00:45:32,349
Now that it's dark...

1128
00:45:32,350 --> 00:45:34,559
- Got it.
- We need to bring them in.

1129
00:45:34,560 --> 00:45:36,420
So they must be brought in before it gets dark.

1130
00:45:38,130 --> 00:45:39,429
It's like Mom bringing...

1131
00:45:39,430 --> 00:45:40,899
the kid back home after school.

1132
00:45:40,900 --> 00:45:41,900
Exactly.

1133
00:45:42,830 --> 00:45:45,670
(Current time: 6pm, 30 minutes before sunset)

1134
00:45:46,570 --> 00:45:49,400
(Meanwhile, the juvenile cows at the pasture are...)

1135
00:45:50,340 --> 00:45:54,880
(enjoying the fresh grass.)

1136
00:45:58,680 --> 00:46:01,449
(It's time to go back home now.)

1137
00:46:01,450 --> 00:46:02,450
(Shouting)

1138
00:46:02,980 --> 00:46:03,989
Does that make them come?

1139
00:46:03,990 --> 00:46:05,420
Yes.

1140
00:46:06,020 --> 00:46:07,120
Let's go.

1141
00:46:09,260 --> 00:46:10,630
Does that really make them come?

1142
00:46:11,990 --> 00:46:13,230
They come if you open the door.

1143
00:46:14,900 --> 00:46:16,559
(Amazed)

1144
00:46:16,560 --> 00:46:17,600
They're coming.

1145
00:46:19,600 --> 00:46:21,470
Let's go.

1146
00:46:21,570 --> 00:46:22,570
Let's go.

1147
00:46:22,571 --> 00:46:24,210
Look at them.

1148
00:46:25,340 --> 00:46:26,340
Here they go.

1149
00:46:28,580 --> 00:46:30,449
(Yodeling)

1150
00:46:30,450 --> 00:46:32,609
(A new kind of yodel cattle driving)

1151
00:46:32,610 --> 00:46:34,149
(Yodeling)

1152
00:46:34,150 --> 00:46:35,150
They're leaving.

1153
00:46:35,580 --> 00:46:38,850
(The cows react to the yodeling?)

1154
00:46:40,050 --> 00:46:42,159
(Yodeling)

1155
00:46:42,160 --> 00:46:44,130
Let's go.

1156
00:46:45,860 --> 00:46:47,129
(Yodeling)

1157
00:46:47,130 --> 00:46:48,529
(Yodeling)

1158
00:46:48,530 --> 00:46:49,999
(Yodeling)

1159
00:46:50,000 --> 00:46:51,799
(Even the CEO is yodeling now.)

1160
00:46:51,800 --> 00:46:53,030
Go straight.

1161
00:46:55,340 --> 00:46:56,769
- Let's go.
- Come now.

1162
00:46:56,770 --> 00:46:57,910
Let's go.

1163
00:46:58,570 --> 00:47:00,070
Hurry.

1164
00:47:00,240 --> 00:47:01,339
(Yodeling)

1165
00:47:01,340 --> 00:47:03,510
(Fancy)

1166
00:47:03,680 --> 00:47:04,750
Come on.

1167
00:47:05,450 --> 00:47:07,549
(Unlike the original fancy yodeling)

1168
00:47:07,550 --> 00:47:09,819
(Yodeling)

1169
00:47:09,820 --> 00:47:12,850
(The imitation sounds quite strange.)

1170
00:47:13,250 --> 00:47:14,320
For some reason,

1171
00:47:15,290 --> 00:47:16,890
it makes me all confident.

1172
00:47:20,960 --> 00:47:22,159
The cows know their way.

1173
00:47:22,160 --> 00:47:23,160
Gosh.

1174
00:47:24,300 --> 00:47:26,130
It's interesting. Seriously.

1175
00:47:28,600 --> 00:47:29,670
It's really interesting.

1176
00:47:30,040 --> 00:47:32,169
They shouldn't go that way, right? No, right?

1177
00:47:32,170 --> 00:47:33,170
(Sneaking away)

1178
00:47:33,340 --> 00:47:34,709
No, stop it.

1179
00:47:34,710 --> 00:47:36,410
(Went off course)

1180
00:47:36,680 --> 00:47:37,880
No, don't go that way.

1181
00:47:39,310 --> 00:47:40,480
Don't eat that.

1182
00:47:43,590 --> 00:47:44,820
Let's go.

1183
00:47:45,950 --> 00:47:47,590
They're super fast.

1184
00:47:49,490 --> 00:47:50,730
Let's go.

1185
00:47:51,190 --> 00:47:54,559
(The cows successfully recalculated their route.)

1186
00:47:54,560 --> 00:47:55,860
(Yodeling)

1187
00:47:57,300 --> 00:47:59,300
- Let's go!
- Let's go.

1188
00:47:59,900 --> 00:48:02,600
- Go in.
- Go.

1189
00:48:03,670 --> 00:48:04,770
Go in.

1190
00:48:06,340 --> 00:48:07,809
(Singing)

1191
00:48:07,810 --> 00:48:08,810
Oh, dear.

1192
00:48:09,940 --> 00:48:13,410
(From the previous cattle shed needed to be cleared of manure)

1193
00:48:15,480 --> 00:48:16,749
Let's go.

1194
00:48:16,750 --> 00:48:18,720
(To a new shed covered in fresh sawdust)

1195
00:48:24,260 --> 00:48:25,890
Let's eat.

1196
00:48:28,330 --> 00:48:31,030
(Enjoying in the clean place)

1197
00:48:31,430 --> 00:48:32,500
Share it.

1198
00:48:33,470 --> 00:48:36,400
(A tasty dinner)

1199
00:48:37,710 --> 00:48:38,710
Okay.

1200
00:48:41,580 --> 00:48:44,309
(Delivering hay after the feed)

1201
00:48:44,310 --> 00:48:47,919
(Ranch tip: Juvenile cows need to fulfill their nutrients...)

1202
00:48:47,920 --> 00:48:51,550
(that cannot be obtained from fresh greens through feed or hay.)

1203
00:48:52,390 --> 00:48:53,820
The cows are so quiet when they eat.

1204
00:48:54,820 --> 00:48:56,190
- After all that mooing.
- Right?

1205
00:48:56,990 --> 00:48:58,559
Seeing them dig in feels rewarding.

1206
00:48:58,560 --> 00:48:59,560
Exactly.

1207
00:49:01,030 --> 00:49:03,260
Somehow, the cows look happier.

1208
00:49:05,170 --> 00:49:06,500
- They're cute.
- Yes.

1209
00:49:06,970 --> 00:49:11,239
(How do you feel after the first technical training?)

1210
00:49:11,240 --> 00:49:12,310
To be honest, today...

1211
00:49:14,610 --> 00:49:16,010
All we did was clean poop.

1212
00:49:16,280 --> 00:49:18,850
(The day was full of poop.)

1213
00:49:19,480 --> 00:49:22,180
Kwang Soo, we don't get a chance to clean poop in our lives.

1214
00:49:22,520 --> 00:49:25,290
- True.
- Unless it's your job.

1215
00:49:25,590 --> 00:49:26,590
So...

1216
00:49:28,060 --> 00:49:30,260
doing something new...

1217
00:49:30,830 --> 00:49:31,890
was fun.

1218
00:49:32,860 --> 00:49:35,299
But won't we be cleaning poop tomorrow and even the day after?

1219
00:49:35,300 --> 00:49:36,499
I doubt it.

1220
00:49:36,500 --> 00:49:38,729
Where the adult cows are.

1221
00:49:38,730 --> 00:49:41,139
It also needs to be checked.

1222
00:49:41,140 --> 00:49:42,140
Wait.

1223
00:49:44,010 --> 00:49:45,410
Isn't this "Poop Poop Farm?"

1224
00:49:47,110 --> 00:49:48,639
Didn't we clean enough poop?

1225
00:49:48,640 --> 00:49:50,280
There must be something else to do.

1226
00:49:52,010 --> 00:49:56,020
(GBRB: Farm Operation - Go Go Farm)

1227
00:49:56,520 --> 00:49:58,690
Sir, what time should we be here tomorrow?

1228
00:49:59,220 --> 00:50:01,489
- Tomorrow would be six.
- Six o'clock?

1229
00:50:01,490 --> 00:50:03,259
Our work starts at 6am.

1230
00:50:03,260 --> 00:50:04,689
(6 in the morning?)

1231
00:50:04,690 --> 00:50:05,930
Then we should get here by 6am.

1232
00:50:07,260 --> 00:50:09,999
- I'm from Pyeongchang.
- I see.

1233
00:50:10,000 --> 00:50:11,299
The honorary ambassador of Pyeongchang was...

1234
00:50:11,300 --> 00:50:13,299
That's right, for the Pyeongchang Winter Games.

1235
00:50:13,300 --> 00:50:14,839
I was the honorary ambassador.

1236
00:50:14,840 --> 00:50:16,370
- Thank you.
- Don't mention it.

1237
00:50:17,410 --> 00:50:18,710
- Are you from Pyeongchang?
- Yes.

1238
00:50:19,140 --> 00:50:20,479
My hometown is Pyeongchang.

1239
00:50:20,480 --> 00:50:22,009
- Is that so?
- Yes.

1240
00:50:22,010 --> 00:50:23,810
Why is that...

1241
00:50:24,780 --> 00:50:27,549
I performed at the closing ceremony of the Pyeongchang Winter Games.

1242
00:50:27,550 --> 00:50:30,389
Pyeongchang was really nice when I visited.

1243
00:50:30,390 --> 00:50:31,789
- Covered in snow, right?
- Yes.

1244
00:50:31,790 --> 00:50:33,859
(And one trainee feels uneasy.)

1245
00:50:33,860 --> 00:50:35,460
- Over there...
- When I was little,

1246
00:50:35,790 --> 00:50:37,290
my name used to be Lee Pyeong Chang.

1247
00:50:37,790 --> 00:50:38,790
It used to be my name.

1248
00:50:39,530 --> 00:50:40,530
I see.

1249
00:50:41,160 --> 00:50:43,970
(Kwang Soo even changed his name, but the CEO is uninterested.)

1250
00:50:45,430 --> 00:50:47,169
What now? Grab food and take a rest?

1251
00:50:47,170 --> 00:50:48,170
That's right.

1252
00:50:48,270 --> 00:50:49,370
What are you having today?

1253
00:50:49,670 --> 00:50:51,239
I need to cook for my wife.

1254
00:50:51,240 --> 00:50:52,869
- Really?
- You cook for her?

1255
00:50:52,870 --> 00:50:53,879
I'm quite the cook.

1256
00:50:53,880 --> 00:50:55,139
What will you cook for her?

1257
00:50:55,140 --> 00:50:59,250
Potatoes, since we're from Gangwon Province.

1258
00:51:00,450 --> 00:51:01,919
We used to cook a lot of potatoes.

1259
00:51:01,920 --> 00:51:04,450
(Suddenly, past memories come to mind.)

1260
00:51:04,690 --> 00:51:06,889
- Six in the morning tomorrow?
- Yes.

1261
00:51:06,890 --> 00:51:08,289
- Great work today.
- Well done.

1262
00:51:08,290 --> 00:51:09,789
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

1263
00:51:09,790 --> 00:51:10,890
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

1264
00:51:12,690 --> 00:51:14,730
Now that we're out here, I don't think it smells.

1265
00:51:14,860 --> 00:51:15,860
Right?

1266
00:51:16,060 --> 00:51:18,530
(The three have come for dinner.)

1267
00:51:19,870 --> 00:51:21,239
Yes, that's right.

1268
00:51:21,240 --> 00:51:22,540
I heard it was amazing.

1269
00:51:23,000 --> 00:51:24,069
(Looking tired)

1270
00:51:24,070 --> 00:51:25,409
Why did you lose so much weight, Kwang Soo?

1271
00:51:25,410 --> 00:51:26,510
I have no idea.

1272
00:51:26,940 --> 00:51:28,180
To be honest, earlier...

1273
00:51:28,740 --> 00:51:30,749
I debated on whether to say this or not, but I'm going to.

1274
00:51:30,750 --> 00:51:32,710
I nearly passed out while peeing just now.

1275
00:51:35,280 --> 00:51:36,750
I held on to the wall while peeing.

1276
00:51:37,520 --> 00:51:40,349
Something might happen to me.

1277
00:51:40,350 --> 00:51:42,289
- It's...
- You look drained.

1278
00:51:42,290 --> 00:51:44,259
It might be the toxins from the poop,

1279
00:51:44,260 --> 00:51:45,630
but I have no idea what's going on with me.

1280
00:51:46,330 --> 00:51:48,430
Why did we come to Jeju Island if we're just going to clean poop?

1281
00:51:49,500 --> 00:51:51,099
There's plenty of poop even in Seoul.

1282
00:51:51,100 --> 00:51:53,370
(There's plenty of poop even in Seoul.)

1283
00:51:53,840 --> 00:51:55,470
(Sniffing)

1284
00:51:55,870 --> 00:51:57,609
I smell really bad.

1285
00:51:57,610 --> 00:51:58,770
Kyung Soo, did you wash your hands?

1286
00:51:59,140 --> 00:52:00,539
- I don't think you did.
- He didn't.

1287
00:52:00,540 --> 00:52:02,079
Go and wash your hands.

1288
00:52:02,080 --> 00:52:03,379
- But I did.
- Seriously?

1289
00:52:03,380 --> 00:52:05,050
- When?
- You washed them back there.

1290
00:52:05,550 --> 00:52:07,950
- Mind your manners, Kyung Soo.
- That's...

1291
00:52:08,280 --> 00:52:10,150
- You...
- My hands smell of soap.

1292
00:52:11,820 --> 00:52:12,820
They smell of poop.

1293
00:52:13,920 --> 00:52:15,889
(Speechless)

1294
00:52:15,890 --> 00:52:16,890
Go wash your hands.

1295
00:52:19,930 --> 00:52:23,230
(While Kyung Soo has gone to wash his hands)

1296
00:52:24,130 --> 00:52:25,369
(Sniffing)

1297
00:52:25,370 --> 00:52:26,569
You can't help but sniff, right?

1298
00:52:26,570 --> 00:52:28,400
I keep checking.

1299
00:52:28,700 --> 00:52:30,510
- It's like...
- What's the psychology behind it?

1300
00:52:30,810 --> 00:52:32,969
Are we praying that we don't smell?

1301
00:52:32,970 --> 00:52:35,009
I can't believe... No, wait.

1302
00:52:35,010 --> 00:52:36,139
(Thinking)

1303
00:52:36,140 --> 00:52:37,979
Am I checking to see if I smell less than earlier?

1304
00:52:37,980 --> 00:52:39,750
I don't understand why I'm doing it.

1305
00:52:40,250 --> 00:52:42,249
- Am I right?
- Sort of.

1306
00:52:42,250 --> 00:52:43,250
I know for sure that I smell.

1307
00:52:43,251 --> 00:52:45,150
- For real.
- But...

1308
00:52:47,120 --> 00:52:49,990
(He can't stop.)

1309
00:52:50,490 --> 00:52:52,189
Isn't it addictive? You just keep smelling it.

1310
00:52:52,190 --> 00:52:53,389
Rather than addictive...

1311
00:52:53,390 --> 00:52:54,799
I don't know why I'm doing it either.

1312
00:52:54,800 --> 00:52:56,599
"Addictive" isn't a word I want to use...

1313
00:52:56,600 --> 00:52:58,430
- here.
- My sides hurt.

1314
00:52:59,200 --> 00:53:01,400
What could this be? Why am I...

1315
00:53:02,140 --> 00:53:03,639
What's wrong with me?

1316
00:53:03,640 --> 00:53:05,670
Like being addicted to the smell of a puppy's paw.

1317
00:53:07,170 --> 00:53:10,179
But the thing is, the smell of a puppy's paw...

1318
00:53:10,180 --> 00:53:11,879
- isn't bad.
- No.

1319
00:53:11,880 --> 00:53:13,549
It smells like warm corn chips.

1320
00:53:13,550 --> 00:53:15,650
No matter who smells this, they'll hate it.

1321
00:53:16,950 --> 00:53:18,750
And yet, what's gotten into me?

1322
00:53:19,590 --> 00:53:23,990
(Kwang Soo has been sucked into the smell of poop.)

1323
00:53:24,860 --> 00:53:25,860
It looks good.

1324
00:53:26,630 --> 00:53:27,899
The portions are huge.

1325
00:53:27,900 --> 00:53:28,900
(The food has arrived.)

1326
00:53:29,500 --> 00:53:30,700
They look delicious.

1327
00:53:31,400 --> 00:53:32,430
It's...

1328
00:53:34,240 --> 00:53:35,369
