1585
01:03:14,950 --> 01:03:17,119
(Nervous)

1586
01:03:17,120 --> 01:03:21,389
(Kwang Soo, 15 Kyung Soo, 36)

1587
01:03:21,390 --> 01:03:24,789
(Woo Bin, 5)

1588
01:03:24,790 --> 01:03:25,830
Yes!

1589
01:03:26,630 --> 01:03:27,729
(Yes!)

1590
01:03:27,730 --> 01:03:30,160
(He's the 1st to decide the order of showering tomorrow.)

1591
01:03:31,470 --> 01:03:32,869
What time do we have to be there?

1592
01:03:32,870 --> 01:03:34,299
We must leave at 5:40am.

1593
01:03:34,300 --> 01:03:36,600
We have to be there by 6am, so we'll leave at 5:40am.

1594
01:03:37,910 --> 01:03:39,170
What time will you take it?

1595
01:03:39,370 --> 01:03:40,510
My shower?

1596
01:03:41,440 --> 01:03:44,439
I need time to prepare myself after the shower,

1597
01:03:44,440 --> 01:03:45,650
so I have to shower at 5am.

1598
01:03:46,180 --> 01:03:47,310
Then I'll take it at 4:40am.

1599
01:03:50,450 --> 01:03:51,450
And you...

1600
01:03:52,950 --> 01:03:56,589
(The one who has to get up the earliest)

1601
01:03:56,590 --> 01:03:58,560
He has to get up around 3:50am.

1602
01:03:58,660 --> 01:03:59,729
That's great.

1603
01:03:59,730 --> 01:04:00,760
This is really great.

1604
01:04:01,800 --> 01:04:03,730
Either way, I'm sharing the room with you.

1605
01:04:04,870 --> 01:04:06,470
I'll turn on the lights as soon as I get up.

1606
01:04:08,770 --> 01:04:10,770
I'll wake up when you turn on the lights.

1607
01:04:12,770 --> 01:04:13,770
You shouldn't wake up.

1608
01:04:16,780 --> 01:04:18,110
I don't mean to wake you up.

1609
01:04:18,250 --> 01:04:20,449
(Pure shamelessness)

1610
01:04:20,450 --> 01:04:21,680
What time will you shower?

1611
01:04:23,250 --> 01:04:24,280
At 5am?

1612
01:04:26,150 --> 01:04:27,720
I'll go in now and shower until 5am.

1613
01:04:28,020 --> 01:04:29,789
(Abuse of power by today's 1st-place shower winner)

1614
01:04:29,790 --> 01:04:30,890
Let's suffer together.

1615
01:04:31,490 --> 01:04:32,490
All of us.

1616
01:04:33,360 --> 01:04:35,300
Do you mind if I go in the bathroom with my blanket?

1617
01:04:36,230 --> 01:04:38,900
(He declares his ownership of the bathroom.)

1618
01:04:39,730 --> 01:04:42,000
I should prepare my outfit for tomorrow.

1619
01:04:42,770 --> 01:04:44,000
Shall we unpack first?

1620
01:04:44,540 --> 01:04:47,310
(After a long game, they finally take a break.)

1621
01:04:49,980 --> 01:04:52,109
(Checking the smell)

1622
01:04:52,110 --> 01:04:53,680
(Double-checking)

1623
01:04:54,550 --> 01:04:55,819
(Exclaiming)

1624
01:04:55,820 --> 01:04:57,480
I have to do the laundry now.

1625
01:04:58,150 --> 01:04:59,349
- Laundry?
- Yes.

1626
01:04:59,350 --> 01:05:00,889
(Work clothes in urgent need of washing)

1627
01:05:00,890 --> 01:05:02,420
What? There's another bathroom here.

1628
01:05:02,760 --> 01:05:04,190
- Is that also a bathroom?
- Really?

1629
01:05:04,520 --> 01:05:06,490
Here it is. It's really nice.

1630
01:05:06,730 --> 01:05:07,999
I didn't even know that it was a bathroom.

1631
01:05:08,000 --> 01:05:09,030
(It turns out that there are 2 bathrooms.)

1632
01:05:09,260 --> 01:05:11,369
Then the order of showering...

1633
01:05:11,370 --> 01:05:12,400
It's reset.

1634
01:05:13,070 --> 01:05:14,230
It's not reset.

1635
01:05:15,070 --> 01:05:17,039
(Laughing)

1636
01:05:17,040 --> 01:05:18,339
Of course it's reset.

1637
01:05:18,340 --> 01:05:19,770
You sounded so cold.

1638
01:05:21,680 --> 01:05:22,740
It's reset.

1639
01:05:22,940 --> 01:05:24,610
- How is it reset?
- What?

1640
01:05:24,950 --> 01:05:26,110
It's not reset.

1641
01:05:26,950 --> 01:05:28,379
(Using each of the bathroom)

1642
01:05:28,380 --> 01:05:31,050
(The intense match ended anticlimactically.)

1643
01:05:34,420 --> 01:05:35,420
Sleep well.

1644
01:05:35,990 --> 01:05:37,520
Woo Bin, you'll shower at 5am?

1645
01:05:37,920 --> 01:05:39,759
(The shower order debate isn't over yet.)

1646
01:05:39,760 --> 01:05:41,330
Since there are two bathrooms...

1647
01:05:41,830 --> 01:05:43,159
I don't think it matters.

1648
01:05:43,160 --> 01:05:45,299
Can't two people shower as soon as they get up?

1649
01:05:45,300 --> 01:05:46,330
Exactly.

1650
01:05:46,570 --> 01:05:47,970
Woo Bin and I'll shower at 5am.

1651
01:05:48,070 --> 01:05:49,769
Once I'm done, I'll wake you up.

1652
01:05:49,770 --> 01:05:51,070
That also works.

1653
01:05:51,440 --> 01:05:53,310
(An amicable agreement is reached.)

1654
01:05:53,570 --> 01:05:54,710
Let's sleep for now.

1655
01:05:55,040 --> 01:05:56,080
Sleep well, Kyung Soo.

1656
01:05:56,180 --> 01:05:57,309
- Good night.
- You too.

1657
01:05:57,310 --> 01:05:58,750
Sleep well.

1658
01:05:59,050 --> 01:06:01,150
(After a long day, everyone falls asleep.)

1659
01:06:02,380 --> 01:06:03,950
(Current time: 5am)

1660
01:06:10,890 --> 01:06:13,060
(Woo Bin is the first to get up.)

1661
01:06:13,460 --> 01:06:15,729
(In the early morning when it's still dark)

1662
01:06:15,730 --> 01:06:17,529
(Heavy footsteps)

1663
01:06:17,530 --> 01:06:20,130
(He heads to the opposite room.)

1664
01:06:21,200 --> 01:06:22,370
- Kwang Soo.
- Yes?

1665
01:06:23,940 --> 01:06:25,470
I'm really tired.

1666
01:06:25,570 --> 01:06:26,570
Right?

1667
01:06:27,140 --> 01:06:28,780
We went to bed so late last night.

1668
01:06:29,740 --> 01:06:32,810
If we went to bed earlier, would we have fallen asleep earlier?

1669
01:06:33,180 --> 01:06:34,180
Yes.

1670
01:06:34,210 --> 01:06:35,720
(Chuckling)

1671
01:06:38,820 --> 01:06:41,490
(He gets ready for work while feeling tired.)

1672
01:06:41,890 --> 01:06:43,519
(On the other hand, Kwang Soo)

1673
01:06:43,520 --> 01:06:44,560
Kyung Soo, get some more sleep.

1674
01:06:45,090 --> 01:06:46,090
Okay.

1675
01:06:46,460 --> 01:06:48,429
(Making a quiet remark)

1676
01:06:48,430 --> 01:06:49,830
You're sleeping well, right?

1677
01:06:50,030 --> 01:06:52,000
(His goal was simply disrupting his sleep.)

1678
01:06:52,900 --> 01:06:54,169
(Getting up)

1679
01:06:54,170 --> 01:06:56,170
Go back to sleep. Don't worry about me.

1680
01:06:56,570 --> 01:06:57,669
Lie back down.

1681
01:06:57,670 --> 01:07:00,070
(Disruption 1: He forces the blanket on him.)

1682
01:07:00,470 --> 01:07:02,580
I'll turn on the lights, so stay sleeping.

1683
01:07:02,840 --> 01:07:07,049
(Disruption 2: Threatening to turn on the lights)

1684
01:07:07,050 --> 01:07:08,220
Go and take a shower.

1685
01:07:08,950 --> 01:07:11,850
(After persistent urging, he finally goes away.)

1686
01:07:16,660 --> 01:07:19,389
(But the sleep disruptor returns soon.)

1687
01:07:19,390 --> 01:07:20,390
What?

1688
01:07:22,660 --> 01:07:23,860
I put some toothpaste on your toothbrush.

1689
01:07:24,430 --> 01:07:25,500
Brush your teeth before going back to sleep.

1690
01:07:26,030 --> 01:07:27,030
Or you'll get cavities.

1691
01:07:27,630 --> 01:07:28,739
Brush your teeth first.

1692
01:07:28,740 --> 01:07:29,740
(Disruption 3: Advising him to brush his teeth)

1693
01:07:30,140 --> 01:07:32,440
(After checking the laundry,)

1694
01:07:32,540 --> 01:07:33,839
(he appears again.)

1695
01:07:33,840 --> 01:07:34,940
Stop looking at your phone and go to sleep.

1696
01:07:37,540 --> 01:07:38,710
You'll be too tired to last today.

1697
01:07:39,110 --> 01:07:40,110
Go back to sleep.

1698
01:07:43,120 --> 01:07:47,090
(He ended up making Kyung Soo get up.)

1699
01:07:47,590 --> 01:07:49,660
(Current time: 5:40am)

1700
01:07:49,760 --> 01:07:51,959
(It's time to go to work.)

1701
01:07:51,960 --> 01:07:53,590
I need to put on my work clothes.

1702
01:07:56,100 --> 01:07:57,829
(Stopping)

1703
01:07:57,830 --> 01:07:59,230
My work clothes...

1704
01:07:59,600 --> 01:08:01,330
- They smell like manure, right?
- Yes.

1705
01:08:02,140 --> 01:08:03,340
It can't be helped.

1706
01:08:04,600 --> 01:08:06,340
- Gosh.
- Is the smell strong?

1707
01:08:07,370 --> 01:08:09,209
(Scent testing)

1708
01:08:09,210 --> 01:08:11,110
(Screaming)

1709
01:08:11,310 --> 01:08:12,410
Anyway,

1710
01:08:13,610 --> 01:08:14,610
I'll get more on it.

1711
01:08:15,420 --> 01:08:16,979
(Trying hard to stay calm)

1712
01:08:16,980 --> 01:08:18,119
(Approaching quietly)

1713
01:08:18,120 --> 01:08:19,250
Stay away from me.

1714
01:08:21,120 --> 01:08:22,120
Oh, come on.

1715
01:08:22,121 --> 01:08:24,460
(The younger one wants to share the strong fragrance.)

1716
01:08:24,830 --> 01:08:26,629
- Woo Bin.
- Yes?

1717
01:08:26,630 --> 01:08:27,860
My jacket smells like manure.

1718
01:08:28,230 --> 01:08:29,260
It's no joke.

1719
01:08:29,530 --> 01:08:30,600
Seriously?

1720
01:08:31,430 --> 01:08:32,900
It's the source of all stench.

1721
01:08:33,630 --> 01:08:36,040
The car smelled bad yesterday because of Kyung Soo.

1722
01:08:36,300 --> 01:08:38,000
- Let me see.
- No.

1723
01:08:38,610 --> 01:08:39,810
Go ahead and smell him.

1724
01:08:40,270 --> 01:08:41,509
(Swinging)

1725
01:08:41,510 --> 01:08:43,240
Let me smell it.

1726
01:08:43,480 --> 01:08:45,380
- Gosh. You're right.
- It smells, right?

1727
01:08:45,680 --> 01:08:46,809
I can't help it.

1728
01:08:46,810 --> 01:08:47,810
How...

1729
01:08:47,811 --> 01:08:49,319
What can I do about it?

1730
01:08:49,320 --> 01:08:51,350
It smells different from the manure yesterday.

1731
01:08:51,820 --> 01:08:54,450
Doesn't it smell like human poop?

1732
01:09:01,030 --> 01:09:02,060
Don't smell me there.

1733
01:09:02,700 --> 01:09:03,759
Goodness.

1734
01:09:03,760 --> 01:09:06,170
I'll put on the jacket at the ranch instead.

1735
01:09:06,970 --> 01:09:09,570
(He leaves it quietly in the back seat.)

1736
01:09:10,440 --> 01:09:14,439
Woo Bin, did you dress up today or what?

1737
01:09:14,440 --> 01:09:17,240
Why would you wear white when it's so easy to stain?

1738
01:09:18,150 --> 01:09:20,110
Even if I get smeared with manure,

1739
01:09:21,150 --> 01:09:23,550
shouldn't I be considerate of the viewers?

1740
01:09:25,050 --> 01:09:27,290
Unlike someone who puts back on a jacket with manure.

1741
01:09:28,020 --> 01:09:29,690
- That's not proper.
- It smells so strong.

1742
01:09:29,790 --> 01:09:31,289
He doesn't make any effort.

1743
01:09:31,290 --> 01:09:33,860
It's not about effort. That's being a nuisance.

1744
01:09:35,360 --> 01:09:36,860
He's Admirable Kyung Soo.

1745
01:09:41,540 --> 01:09:42,569
(He spots Admirable Kyung Soo's jacket.)

1746
01:09:42,570 --> 01:09:43,600
Darn it.

1747
01:09:46,470 --> 01:09:47,840
Hurry up and get in.

1748
01:09:49,080 --> 01:09:50,240
He's not...

1749
01:09:51,480 --> 01:09:53,009
He's not usually like that.

1750
01:09:53,010 --> 01:09:54,180
Why does he act like this when he's here?

1751
01:09:56,920 --> 01:09:58,989
Are you saying that I smell like poop?

1752
01:09:58,990 --> 01:10:00,449
- What?
- Is that what you're saying?

1753
01:10:00,450 --> 01:10:02,920
Do you usually smell bad?

1754
01:10:03,220 --> 01:10:04,520
I don't smell.

1755
01:10:04,760 --> 01:10:05,790
Goodness.

1756
01:10:07,260 --> 01:10:08,530
I saw smoke rising from it.

1757
01:10:09,360 --> 01:10:10,360
I'm serious.

1758
01:10:10,460 --> 01:10:12,369
(He hesitates to get in the back seat.)

1759
01:10:12,370 --> 01:10:13,800
Kwang Soo, I'll sit in the front.

1760
01:10:17,440 --> 01:10:19,009
Please head to the ranch.

1761
01:10:19,010 --> 01:10:20,140
- Okay.
- Okay.

1762
01:10:22,080 --> 01:10:25,009
(A few minutes after KKPP workers leave for work)

1763
01:10:25,010 --> 01:10:29,720
(Jeju International Airport)

1764
01:10:30,180 --> 01:10:31,180
- What?
- Gosh.

1765
01:10:36,560 --> 01:10:39,190
- Hello.
- Hello.

1766
01:10:39,360 --> 01:10:41,329
- You came out early.
- You came out early.

1767
01:10:41,330 --> 01:10:43,230
- This is great.
- I know.

1768
01:10:44,500 --> 01:10:46,430
I see. Okay.

1769
01:10:46,630 --> 01:10:48,299
- Should I sit in the front?
- Go ahead.

1770
01:10:48,300 --> 01:10:50,370
You said that it was KKPP.

1771
01:10:51,000 --> 01:10:52,870
I expected myself to work,

1772
01:10:54,540 --> 01:10:56,439
but I didn't know I'd be an intern.

1773
01:10:56,440 --> 01:10:57,809
(Intern Moon Sang Hoon at KKPP Food)

1774
01:10:57,810 --> 01:10:59,479
- You seem disappointed.
- No, I'm not,

1775
01:10:59,480 --> 01:11:01,250
but I'm a little worried.

1776
01:11:01,350 --> 01:11:03,049
Normally, you're very close to CEO Kwang Soo.

1777
01:11:03,050 --> 01:11:05,089
You're practically brothers.

1778
01:11:05,090 --> 01:11:06,249
Right.

1779
01:11:06,250 --> 01:11:08,389
When you get there, he'll be the CEO.

1780
01:11:08,390 --> 01:11:10,390
Right. I probably can't even look him in the eye.

1781
01:11:11,860 --> 01:11:13,630
I'm used to hierarchy.

1782
01:11:13,990 --> 01:11:15,360
In fact, I prefer it.

1783
01:11:15,700 --> 01:11:17,260
I'm a chimpanzee-type of person.

1784
01:11:17,630 --> 01:11:19,229
Like a chimpanzee, I feel more at ease...

1785
01:11:19,230 --> 01:11:20,600
when there's a clear leader.

1786
01:11:21,400 --> 01:11:24,400
(An intern with a chimpanzee-like tendency to submit to authority)

1787
01:11:24,770 --> 01:11:27,840
How should I serve him?

1788
01:11:28,170 --> 01:11:30,609
Honestly, I'm not the type to stand in opposition...

1789
01:11:30,610 --> 01:11:33,609
to powerful people like the CEO.

1790
01:11:33,610 --> 01:11:35,450
I'd much rather be on their side.

1791
01:11:36,020 --> 01:11:37,879
I can see that.

1792
01:11:37,880 --> 01:11:41,089
So I want to be the captain's parrot.

1793
01:11:41,090 --> 01:11:43,720
You know that parrots outrank the first mate, right?

1794
01:11:45,160 --> 01:11:46,859
In some cases, a talented parrot can...

1795
01:11:46,860 --> 01:11:48,560
even control the captain.

1796
01:11:49,300 --> 01:11:52,099
- Right.
- I hope the day never comes...

1797
01:11:52,100 --> 01:11:54,130
when I actually have to say this to the CEO.

1798
01:11:54,600 --> 01:11:56,840
I'm an intern now, but the moment I leave, I become a customer.

1799
01:11:58,470 --> 01:11:59,940
I may be an intern now,

1800
01:12:00,140 --> 01:12:02,339
but as soon as I'm no longer an intern,

1801
01:12:02,340 --> 01:12:03,880
I'm back to being a customer.

1802
01:12:04,510 --> 01:12:06,980
(It turns out this intern has a surprisingly bold side.)

1803
01:12:07,680 --> 01:12:09,379
It feels like transferring to another school.

1804
01:12:09,380 --> 01:12:11,320
- I can see that.
- I'm close to all three of them.

1805
01:12:11,620 --> 01:12:14,149
I'm starting to regret what I said earlier about politics...

1806
01:12:14,150 --> 01:12:15,590
and being the captain's parrot.

1807
01:12:15,890 --> 01:12:17,119
As soon as I arrived,

1808
01:12:17,120 --> 01:12:18,359
I talked with confidence.

1809
01:12:18,360 --> 01:12:19,390
But now that I think about it...

1810
01:12:20,330 --> 01:12:22,029
Why did you change so much?

1811
01:12:22,030 --> 01:12:23,999
You were just dreaming of rebelling as an intern.

1812
01:12:24,000 --> 01:12:25,630
It happened so suddenly.

1813
01:12:27,230 --> 01:12:29,470
- My mouth is bone dry.
- Is one of the cups empty?

1814
01:12:29,570 --> 01:12:31,569
I drank one because I felt very nervous.

1815
01:12:31,570 --> 01:12:33,509
(The closer the meeting gets, the more terrified he becomes.)

1816
01:12:33,510 --> 01:12:34,570
Are we there yet?

1817
01:12:35,740 --> 01:12:37,009
You're about to go in.

1818
01:12:37,010 --> 01:12:38,310
- Is this the lodging?
- Yes.

1819
01:12:38,610 --> 01:12:42,450
(He arrived at the accommodation where his seniors are resting.)

1820
01:12:43,420 --> 01:12:47,050
(The KKPP Food seniors have no idea that the intern is coming.)

1821
01:12:56,500 --> 01:12:57,600
(Opening)

1822
01:12:59,170 --> 01:13:00,270
(Closing)

1823
01:13:03,670 --> 01:13:04,800
Hello.

1824
01:13:05,870 --> 01:13:06,940
Is anyone home?

1825
01:13:09,410 --> 01:13:10,410
I...

1826
01:13:12,210 --> 01:13:15,010
This is Moon Sang Hoon, and I'm the intern.

1827
01:13:16,320 --> 01:13:17,750
None of my hands are free.

1828
01:13:25,160 --> 01:13:26,729
Hello, Woo Bin.

1829
01:13:26,730 --> 01:13:27,730
What's going on?

1830
01:13:28,630 --> 01:13:30,900
I came here today as an intern.

1831
01:13:33,200 --> 01:13:36,169
(In the midst of the peaceful KKPP retreat)

1832
01:13:36,170 --> 01:13:38,169
(Woo Bin is flustered.)

1833
01:13:38,170 --> 01:13:41,509
(Please stop insisting me to make myself at home.)

1834
01:13:41,510 --> 01:13:42,840
(It makes me even more uncomfortable.)

1835
01:13:42,940 --> 01:13:45,410
(The arrival of a bold Gen Z intern)

1836
01:13:45,580 --> 01:13:47,609
(Intern's breath 1, extraordinary task-handling skills)

1837
01:13:47,610 --> 01:13:48,880
(You're the one who thought of the ventilator, right?)

1838
01:13:49,150 --> 01:13:51,620
(Pleased by the competent intern)

1839
01:13:52,050 --> 01:13:54,050
(You seem to be the real power player here.)

1840
01:13:54,150 --> 01:13:55,160
(Water to flatter him)

1841
01:13:56,290 --> 01:13:58,360
(Intern's breath 2, quickly identifying who holds power)

1842
01:13:58,690 --> 01:14:00,359
(Everything seems to be going the intern's way.)

1843
01:14:00,360 --> 01:14:02,399
(I was thinking of going to wash my hands.)

1844
01:14:02,400 --> 01:14:03,930
(None of your superiors washed their hands yet.)

1845
01:14:04,030 --> 01:14:06,130
(You're right...)

1846
01:14:06,500 --> 01:14:09,940
(However, earning recognition from the CEO is never easy.)

